>Many of The Post Office’s financial service products are provided in partnership with the Bank of Ireland and the two companies have built a successful partnership over the past decade</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Together we provide a comprehensive range of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">products to 3 million customers and we have a savings book valued at £17 billion.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">4.2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The Bank of Ireland’s UK business was incorporated into a separate ring-fenced UK company on 1 November 2010 which means that depositors are protected under the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Financia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">l Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">4.3 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Bank of Ireland </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">personal, business and basic bank account </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">customers can access cash withdrawal</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, balance enquir</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ies,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> cash and cheque deposit services at Post Office counters.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> We also provide BOI business custome